{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was just what happened in Switzerland, when the Swiss had a-- a Soviet delegation or Soviet people who they had imprisoned in Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they exchanged them for-- for the two diplomats.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I think, in a way, perhaps, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the main reason for them to arrest Raoul Wallenberg was that they suspected him to be an agent, a spy, perhaps not only for the Americans.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because they knew that these connections we had with the Americans the whole time, you know, and the financial aid-- aid and all that we got.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But also, when they found that he had meetings with Eichmann and all that, they said to themselves, oh, of course.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- as I told you the story, we liberated the Jewish people and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think the answer to that is that they were very, very anxious not to violate the relationship, the diplomatic relationship with Sweden.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They needed Sweden, up in the north, as a neutral country, as a breathing hole.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I also think that the-- Himmler and those-- and those people, already at that time was thinking of, perhaps, one day, we could use Sweden as an intermediary to get a peace treaty with the Allies, perhaps, behind the backs of the-- of the Soviets, as well.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, a very unrealistic idea, of course.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But anyhow-- so he was sort of having that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He is buying all the-- So I'm-- I'm-- I'm quite sure that the Germans in Budapest had a kind of a standing instructions not to-- to-- to be very careful about this and not to violate the Swedish delegation, or the Swedish mission and all that.",
      "word_count": 46
    }
  ],
